objecttypes.name: Well
objecttypes.description: The origin of a set of wellbores.

objecttypes.name: WellLog
objecttypes.description: A well log is a data type that correlates a particular measurement or multiple measurements in a wellbore against depth and/or time within that wellbore. When plotted visually, well logs are typically long line graphs (called "curves") but may sometimes be discrete points or intervals. This schema object is intended for digital well logs, not raster log files or raster calibration files, but may be used for the latter in the absence of a defined OSDU schema for these use cases.

properties.name: LogSource
properties.description: OSDU Native Log Source - will be updated for later releases - not to be used yet

properties.name: LogActivity
properties.description: Log Activity, used to describe the type of pass such as Calibration Pass - Main Pass - Repeated Pass

properties.name: LogRun
properties.description: Log Run - describe the run of the log - can be a number, but may be also a alphanumeric description such as a version name

properties.name: LogVersion
properties.description: Log Version

properties.name: LoggingService
properties.description: Logging Service - mainly a short concatenation of the names of the tools

properties.name: ToolStringDescription
properties.description: Tool String Description - a long concatenation of the tools used for logging services such as GammaRay+NeutronPorosity

properties.name: LoggingDirection
properties.description: Specifies whether curves were collected downward or upward

properties.name: DrillingFluidProperty
properties.description: Type of mud at time of logging (oil, water based,...)

properties.name: HoleTypeLogging
properties.description: Description of the hole related type of logging - POSSIBLE VALUE : OpenHole / CasedHole / CementedHole

properties.name: FrameIdentifier
properties.description: For multi-frame or multi-section files, this identifier defines the source frame in the file. If the identifier is an index number the index starts with zero and is converted to a string for this property.

properties.name: ZeroTime
properties.description: Optional time reference for (calender) time logs. The ISO date time string representing zero time. Not to be confused with seismic travel time zero. The latter is defined by SeismicReferenceDatum.

properties.name: LogRemark
properties.description: Log remark provides contextual information during the actual log object acquisition. Explains how the measurement in the wellbore is taken on a point in time or depth. Additional information may be included such as bad weather, tool failure, etc. Usually a part of the log header, log remark contains info specific for an acquisition run, specific for a given logging tool (multiple measurements) and/or a specific interval. In essence, log remark represents the external factors and operational environment, directly or indirectly affecting the measurement quality/uncertainty (dynamically over time/depth) - adding both noise and bias to the measurements.

objecttypes.name: WellPlanningWell
objecttypes.description: Information about a single well. A well is a unique surface location from which wellbores are drilled into the Earth for the purpose of either (1) finding or producing underground resources; or (2) providing services related to the production of underground resources.

properties.name: TimeZone
properties.description: The UTC time zone in which  well is located - expressed as ISO 8601.

properties.name: TypeWell
properties.description: Proposed values : Mining, Petroleum, Scientific, Geothermal, Storage, Surface Coring, Water well

properties.name: LicenceName
properties.description: Legal name of the well as described within the Licence

properties.name: LicenceNumber
properties.description: License number of the well

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Name of Well Planning well. Derived from the record identified by WellID.

objecttypes.name: WellPlanningWellbore
objecttypes.description: A hole in the ground extending from a point at the earth's surface to the maximum point of penetration.

properties.name: Name
properties.description: Name of Well Planning wellbore. Derived from the record identified by WellboreID.

objecttypes.name: Wellbore
objecttypes.description: A hole in the ground extending from a point at the earth's surface to the maximum point of penetration.

properties.name: KickOffWellbore
properties.description: This is a pointer to the parent wellbore. The wellbore that starts from top has no parent.

properties.name: TargetFormation
properties.description: The Formation of interest for which the Wellbore is drilled to interact with. The Wellbore may terminate in a lower formation if the requirement is to drill through the entirety of the target formation, therefore this is not necessarily the Formation at TD.

objecttypes.name: WellboreMarkerSet
objecttypes.description: Wellbore Markers identify the depth in a wellbore, measured below a reference elevation, at which a person or an automated process identifies a noteworthy observation, which is usually a change in the rock that intersects that wellbore. Formation Marker data includes attributes/properties that put these depths in context. Formation Markers are sometimes known as picks or formation tops.

objecttypes.name: WellboreTrajectory
objecttypes.description: Work Product Component describing an individual instance of a wellbore trajectory data object. Also called a deviation survey, wellbore trajectory is data that is used to calculate the position and spatial uncertainty of a planned or actual wellbore in 2-dimensional and 3-dimensional space.

objects.name: AppliedOperations
objects.description: The audit trail of operations applied to the station coordinates from the original state to the current state. The list may contain operations applied prior to ingestion as well as the operations applied to produce the Wgs84Coordinates. The text elements refer to ESRI style CRS and Transformation names, which may have to be translated to EPSG standard names.

objects.name: CurveDescription
objects.description: Mnemonic-level curve description is used during parsing or reading and ingesting LAS or DLIS files, to explain the type of measurement being looked at, specifically for that moment. Curve description is specific to that single (log) mnemonic and for the entire log (acquisition run) interval. In essence, curve description defines the internal factors such as what the "curve" or measurement ideally is representing, how is it calculated, what are the assumptions and the "constants".

objects.title: WellboreTrajectory

objects.name: ZeroTime
objects.description: Optional time reference for (calender) time logs. The ISO date time string representing zero time. Not to be confused with seismic travel time zero. The latter is defined by SeismicReferenceDatum.

objects.name: hasActivityType
objects.description: General method or circumstance of logging - MWD, completion, ...

objects.name: hasAzimuthReferenceType
objects.description: The North reference of the trajectory used to define the azimuth angular measurement values. For example, True North, Grid North, Magnetic North.
objects.title: Azimuth Reference Type

objects.name: hasBlockID
objects.description: Identifier of the Geopolitical Entity that describes the Block associated to the Licence
objects.title: Block ID

objects.name: hasCalculationMethodType
objects.description: Calculation Method Type used to compute the TVD, X OFFSET, Y OFFSET and DOG LEG SEVERITY values for this Directional Survey. For example, Radius of Curvature, Minimum Curvature, Balanced Tangential, etc.
objects.title: Calculation Method Type

objects.name: hasCandidateReferenceCurveIDs
objects.description: Secondary index curves, which are alternative candidates to act as ReferenceCurveID. Generally not populated, except in the cases where multiple reference curves are present, e.g. measured depth and time.

objects.name: hasCompanyID
objects.description: The relationship to company who engaged the service company (ServiceCompanyID) to perform the logging.
objects.title: Company ID

objects.name: hasCompanyID
objects.description: The relationship to company who engaged the service company (ServiceCompanyID) to perform the surveying.
objects.title: Company ID

objects.name: hasCurveID
objects.description: The ID of the Well Log Curve

objects.name: hasCurveSampleTypeID
objects.description: The value type to be expected as curve sample values.
objects.title: Curve Sample Type ID

objects.name: hasDefaultVerticalCRSID
objects.description: The default vertical coordinate reference system used in the vertical measurements for a well or wellbore if absent from input vertical measurements and there is no other recourse for obtaining a valid CRS.

objects.name: hasDefaultVerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The default datum reference point, or zero depth point, used to determine other points vertically in a well.  References an entry in the VerticalMeasurements array.

objects.name: hasDefaultVerticalMeasurementID
objects.description: The default datum reference point, or zero depth point, used to determine other points vertically in a wellbore.  References an entry in the Vertical Measurements array of this wellbore.

objects.name: hasDefinitiveTrajectoryID
objects.description: SRN of Wellbore Trajectory which is considered the authoritative or preferred version.

objects.name: hasFeatureTypeID
objects.description: Feature Type Reference Type. Possible values - Base, top, fault, salt, reef, sea floor

objects.name: hasGeographicCRSID
objects.description: Coordinate Reference System defining the Geodetic Datum of the station LATITUDE and LONGITUDE values. If LATITUDE and LONGITUDE attributes are stored, clearly identifying their Datum is required.
objects.title: Geographic Coordinate Reference System

objects.name: hasHoleSectionID
objects.description: The definitive description of the hole section associated with this wellbore
objects.title: Hole Section ID

objects.name: hasInterestTypeID
objects.description: Pre-defined reasons for interest in the well or information about the well.

objects.name: hasInterpretationID
objects.description: The optional relationship to a HorizonInterpretation, GeobodyBoundaryInterpretation or FaultInterpretation.
objects.title: Interpretation ID

objects.name: hasLogCurveBusinessValueID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Business Value Type.

objects.name: hasLogCurveFamilyID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Family - which is the detailed Geological Physical Quantity Measured - such as neutron porosity

objects.name: hasLogCurveMainFamilyID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Main Family Type - which is the Geological Physical Quantity measured - such as porosity.

objects.name: hasLogCurveTypeID
objects.description: The related record id of the Log Curve Type - which is the standard mnemonic chosen by the company - OSDU provides an initial list

objects.name: hasMarkerID
objects.description: A unique identifier of the marker in the list of data.Markers[], ideally a UUID. If unpopulated, the string-converted element index number is used. The first index is "0".
objects.title: Marker ID

objects.name: hasMarkerPropertyTypeID
objects.description: The reference to a marker property type - or if interpreted as CSV columns, the 'well-known column type. It is a relationship to a reference-data--MarkerPropertyType record id.
objects.title: Marker Property Type ID

objects.name: hasMarkerPropertyUnitID
objects.description: Unit of Measure for the marker properties of type MarkerPropertyType.
objects.title: Marker Property Unit ID

objects.name: hasMarkerTypeID
objects.description: Marker Type Reference Type. Possible values - Biostratigraphy, Lithostratigraphy, seismic, depth of well, sequence, flow unit

objects.name: hasPPFGDatasetID
objects.description: A reference to the PPFGDataset that holds the information about the pore pressure associated with the definitive drilling program
objects.title: PPFG Dataset ID

objects.name: hasPlannedLithologyID
objects.description: A reference to the descriptive object that holds the information about the planned lithology associated with the wellbore
objects.title: Planned Lithology ID

objects.name: hasPrimaryMaterialID
objects.description: The primary material injected/produced from the wellbore.

objects.name: hasProjectedCRSID
objects.description: Coordinate Reference System defining the Projection of the station EASTING and NORTHING values. If  type is "Grid North" and EASTING and NORTHING attributes are stored, clearly identifying their projection is required.
objects.title: Projected Coordinate Reference System ID

objects.name: hasReferenceCurveID
objects.description: The data.Curves[].CurveID, which holds the primary index (reference) values.
objects.title: Reference Curve ID

objects.name: hasSamplingDomainTypeID
objects.description: The sampling domain, e.g. measured depth, true vertical, travel-time, calendar-time.
objects.title: Sampling Domain Type ID

objects.name: hasServiceCompanyID
objects.description: The relationship to a Service Company, typically the producer or logging contractor.

objects.name: hasServiceCompanyID
objects.description: Name of the Survey Company.
objects.title: Service Company

objects.name: hasStationPropertyUnitID
objects.description: Unit of Measure for the station properties of type TrajectoryStationPropertyType.
objects.title: Station Property Unit ID

objects.name: hasStratigraphicColumnID
objects.description: The optional reference to a stratigraphic column (referring to multiple StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation) providing the stratigraphic framework for the WellboreMarkerSet. It demonstrates the intent to describe complex, potentially overlapping stratigraphic intervals. Only one of the properties StratigraphicColumnID or StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretationID should be populated.
objects.title: Stratigraphic Column ID

objects.name: hasStratigraphicColumnRankInterpretationID
objects.description: The optional reference to a StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretation. It expresses the intent of a stratigraphic framework with non-overlapping intervals. Only one of the properties StratigraphicColumnID or StratigraphicColumnRankInterpretationID should be populated.
objects.title: Stratigraphic Column Rank ID

objects.name: hasSurveyProgramIDs
objects.description: A reference to the objects that holds the information about the definitive version of the different survey programs associated with the wellbore
objects.title: Survey Program IDs

objects.name: hasSurveyToolTypeID
objects.description: The type of tool or equipment used to acquire this Directional Survey.  For example, gyroscopic, magnetic, MWD, TOTCO, acid bottle, etc. Follow OWSG reference data and support the ISCWSA survey tool definitions.
objects.title: Type of the Survey Tool

objects.name: hasSurveyType
objects.description: The type of this directional survey.  For example a "Directional Survey" where MD, Inclination and Azimuth are all measured or a "Position Log" where Inclination and Azimuth are both null and only MD, TVD and X/Y Offsets are available) - or "Full Survey" where everything is fully filled-up, depth-inclination-azimuth.
objects.title: Directional Survey Type

objects.name: hasTargetID
objects.description: The drill targets associated with this definitive Drilling Program
objects.title: Target ID

objects.name: hasTrajectoryStationPropertyTypeID
objects.description: The reference to a trajectory station property type - or if interpreted as channels, the curve or channel name type, identifying e.g. MD, Inclination, Azimuth. This is a relationship to a reference-data--TrajectoryStationPropertyType record id.
objects.title: Trajectory Station Property Type ID

objects.name: hasTrajectoryTypeID
objects.description: Describes the predominant shapes the wellbore path can follow if deviated from vertical. Sample Values: Horizontal, Vertical, Directional.

objects.name: hasWellLogTypeID
objects.description: Well Log Type short Description such as Raw; Evaluated; Composite;....
